        "type": "service",
        "title": "Surface Soil Moisture from Sentinel‑1 using Change Detection",
        "description": "Estimates surface soil moisture (SSM) from Sentinel‑1 GRD data (VV polarisation) based on a change detection method. The algorithm computes the minimum, maximum and mean backscatter over a reference period (e.g., three years), takes the last image of a current observation interval, and applies the formula SSM = (σ⁰_current - σ⁰_min) / (σ⁰_max - σ⁰_min). Urban and permanent water areas are masked out using thresholds on the long‑term mean backscatter in decibels (>‑6 dB or <‑17 dB). The output is a single‑band raster cube with values between 0 (dry) and 1 (wet).",
        "cost_estimate": 4,
        "cost_unit": "platform credits per km²",
